# VGT Versioning Policy

> **Policy Version:** 1.0 | **Created:** 2025 | **Author:** Tsutomu Ishii (Independent Researcher)

This document defines the permanent versioning rules for the Virtual Gravity Theory (VGT) project.

---

## Version Format

All VGT releases use a four-segment system: `V.C.R.S`

| Segment | Meaning |
|---------|---------|
| V | Volume |
| C | Chapter |
| R | Release (0 = Initial, 1 = Minor revision, 2 = Major revision) |
| S | Sub-revision (0, 1, 2, …) |

**Example:** `3.12.1.1` → Volume 3, Chapter 12, Minor revision, patch 1

---

## ZIP Filename

```
VGT_<V.C.R.S>_<YYYY>_<MM>_<DD>.zip
```

**Example:** `VGT_3.12.1.1_2026_03_08.zip`

---

## GitHub Release Tags

Tags use version only (no dates): `v<V.C.R.S>`

**Example:** `v3.12.1.1`

---

## Zenodo DOI

DOI versions must exactly match GitHub tags. The ZIP must be **bit-identical**.

---

## Standard ZIP Contents

| File/Folder | Required |
|-------------|----------|
| `README_DOI.md` | Yes |
| `MANUSCRIPT.pdf` | Yes |
| `MANUSCRIPT.tex` | Yes |
| `figs/` | Yes |
| `CHANGELOG.md` | Yes |
| `CITATION.cff` | Yes |
| `supplementary/` | Optional |

> **Note:** Submission-specific files (e.g., cover letters) must not be included.

---

**Scope:** All VGT Volumes and Chapters
